 # PP&D Supervisor Repair Guide
 
-## Purpose
+This guide is for supervisor-triggered repair cycles only. It is not a PP&D domain backlog and must not be used to implement permit, crawler, extraction, DevHub, or guardrail features directly.
 
-This guide tells the PP&D supervisor how to recover daemon progress when a task is blocked by repeated validation failures. It is intentionally narrow: repair supervision, task selection, retry policy, and diagnostics before asking the worker to attempt another PP&D domain implementation.
+## Syntax and Compile Failure Recovery
 
-## Syntax-First Recovery Policy
+When two recent daemon validation rollbacks include Python `SyntaxError`, `py_compile` failures, or TypeScript parser errors such as `TS1005`, `TS1109`, or `TS1128`, the supervisor repair response must narrow the next worker attempt before any more domain work is requested.
 
-When a recent failed patch reports Python `SyntaxError`, `py_compile` failure, or TypeScript `TS1005`, `TS1109`, or `TS1128`, the next daemon cycle must choose a syntax-first repair task instead of a broad implementation task.
